This spectacular custom-built hilltop brick & stone estate is the absolute best value on the market in all of Vinings! You could not replicate this immaculate property for today’s list price. Featuring an attached and fully-equipped guest house, perfect for multi-generational living or an additional home office. Guests are greeted by custom Mahogany French doors leading into the gracious foyer, flanked by a beautiful curved three-story open staircase and a gracious ensuite guest bedroom, currently used as an office. The designer kitchen features Quartz countertops, raised cabinetry with antique mirror inlay, and adjoining scullery featuring a secondary refrigerator, sink, microwave, and abundance of pantry storage. The spacious fireside keeping room features accordion doors opening to the covered fireside veranda, offering quintessential indoor/outdoor living. The impressive primary suite features a private balcony, a spa-inspired bathroom with dual vanities, make-up vanity, soaking tub, large walk-in shower, and his/her water closets. The palatial walk-in closet impresses with a morning bar, large center island, and hidden door leading to a designer craft room with built-in desk. A vaulted teen suite features a library ladder to a third floor bonus/playroom. The third floor also offers a game room, custom wet bar with live edge stone counters, and a balcony overlooking the wooded backyard. The partial terrace level offers a gym, wine cellar, hobby room, and an abundance of storage. Additional features include a three-stop elevator, garage parking for six cars, turfed yard featuring golf tees and putting green, high efficiency heating and cooling systems, spray foam insulation, fifty-year roof shingles, tankless water heater, circuits for electric car chargers, casement windows, triple locking doors, driveway parking for dozens of cars.

Enjoy the expansive floor plan offering an abundance of living & entertaining spaces. The impressive main level features a gracious entry foyer, beautiful formal dining room, spacious family room featuring vaulted ceilings with skylights, a gas fireplace flanked by built-in shelving, and a light-drenched sunroom ideal for a sitting room or home office. The Lullwater Estate is a beautiful and quiet community located directly across the street from Olmstead Park, and in close proximity to Fernbank Museum, Druid Hills Golf Club Club, Emory University, CDC, and Decatur.

Nestled on a picturesque 1.6+ acre lot on one of Buckhead's most prized streets, this classic Clement Ford-designed traditional home offers tranquility and a stately setting in the heart of Tuxedo Park. A portico prefaces the front entry where a half-moon transom window and a half-lite wooden storm door allow light to spill into the wide foyer. The renovated Poggenpohl kitchen features double Sub-Zero refrigerators and a freezer, a wraparound island, abundant natural light from a wall of windows, and opens to a gorgeous sunroom overlooking the expansive rear grounds. A handsome fireside study with judge’s molding adjoins the spacious, separate formal living room where a fireplace serves as the focal point. The sizable formal dining room seats 12+ guests. The main-level primary suite offers his and her baths with a shared double-entry shower. An additional en suite guest bedroom completes the main level. The second story offers two additional bedroom suites plus a computer room/study off the landing and an additional bonus area. Enjoy two full-size laundry rooms; one on the upper level and a second on the lower level. The expansive terrace level delights with a fireside family room, a second full kitchen, a newly renovated spa-inspired bathroom, an en suite guest bedroom and a bonus room, doubling as a home gym. The terrace level opens to the rear courtyard, offering serene views of the immense, wooded lot. Additional features include an attached two-car garage, a detached two-car garage, and immense storage.

The fully-equipped designer kitchen features an oversized island with quartz countertops, integrated professional appliance package, a separate breakfast room, and opens to the gorgeous fireside family room adorned by a wood-beamed ceiling with skylights. Two bedroom suites complete the main level, including the idyllic fireside primary suite featuring a spa-inspired bathroom with dual vanities, frameless glass walk-in shower, and department store quality custom closet.
